result.name: Sang Kee Congee And Noodles

reviews.text: Good spot for a quick cheap meal. The congee is pretty good. I would not say it is substantially better than most places but definitely above average.  There is usually a really long line during lunch time. I would try avoid peak hours as its definitely not worth waiting a long time for.

Food is pretty good for a congee joint but service is stuck in the 80s. Utensils were not cleaned, when I asked for a change they came back even dirtier with bits of scraps on them. Staff has attitude issues.

They are popular because they managed to get a story on the paper like 20 years ago. Great place if you don't mind sharing small tables with dirty utensils where the staff looks and acts like they hate your mother.
most famous local congee restaurant.  Very tasty and very reasonable.  Must try.
A must-do if u r a Chinese congee lover.  The ingredients are fresh which is important for good congee. The noodles are average though.
Neat little place for quick local congee and noodles. Line up could be quite long during lunch hours. Service is quite quick. Fairly priced.

result.name: Sheng Kee Congee 生记粥面

reviews.text: Place was small and crowded. We walked in just a bit earlier than the queues. Tried beef congee. Staff were impatient and not very helpful with the menu...but delicious food although there was no "ja lerng" (fried dough wrapped in rice noodle with soy sauce).
Great simple place for porridge. Fresh ingredients. Beef slices option is recommended.
Nice local congee and noodles at cheap prices.

就算好食都無用。員工態度超級差。
上次不知道他們一小時內關門，進去叫了碗粥，店員也沒跟我們説七八個字後要關門。粥來了，便不斷在旁邊説難聽的話，「唉，未得啦，都未食完」之類。。。不停説😡。

其實一開始直接告訴我們快要關門，我們可以選擇暫不吃或有心理準備要加快速度。始終阻人收工不好。。。但這樣説難聽的話要人難受，實在太過份。

我以為只是巧合，沒想到跟朋友説起，他也試過，一模一樣! 

你不愁生意你的事，反正我再也不會來，也會告訴身邊人這件事。
名大於實，地方較窄，食物也未如傳說中好味，普通。
